arch:property.oc:show_val: A small bone assemblage was recovered from this unit and mainly from the flotation sample. Burnt bone is rare and the majority of the bone is unidentifiable bone splinters of 03 sized animals. One piece of bird was recovered from the dry sieve material. Some fish and microfauna were present in the flotation sample. An additional bag of dry sieve contained a probable cat metapodial and a few pieces of caprine bone. Also a pathological sheep/goat jaw that displays swelling under the erupting P4. Last number = 108
